g.text: Same AddressVersion: 0.3AF_XDP shares the following between user process and Kernel•RX/TX Rings•Fill/Completion Queues•UMEM area, which is the Mempool buffers area•All areas are mmap’dbetween kernel and user processRX Flow:•Examine RX ring for received packet buffers (found N pkts)•Remove the N packets/buffers from RX Ring•Allocate N buffers/mbufsfrom the RX Mempool•Add the N buffers to the fill queue (FQ)TX Flow:•User allocates buffers from TX Mempool (creates packets)•User can also use RX Ring buffers (i.e.forwarding)•Add buffers to the TX Ring from application•Look at the Completion queue (CQ) for completed TX buffers•Free the TX buffers back to the TX Mempool
